article.headline: Florida State 71, Bowling Green 60
article.story: MOBILE, Ala. (AP) -- Todd Galloway scored 14 points and Alexander Johnson added 12, leading Florida State to a 71-60 victory in the second round of Saturday's Coors Classic. Galloways hit 8 of 11 free throws for the Seminoles (6-1), while Johnson connected on 5 of 10 from the line. Jason Rich added 10 points, while Al Thornton had 9 points and grabbed a game-high 10 rebounds. The Falcons (2-6) were led by Martin Samarco, who had a game-high 27 points that included seven 3-pointers. Steven Wright added 12 points and Matt Lefeld had 10. After leading by two points at halftime, Florida State outscored Bowling Green 41-32 in the second half. The Falcons were held to 38.5 percent shooting, while Florida State hit 46.2 percent of its shots. Earlier in the evening, South Alabama took a 66-62 victory over No. 25 Houston.
